David-
I use a high temperature powdercoat
product for engine tin application.
When paint is required, consider
PPG DP-90 epoxy primer.
It is standard shelf material.
DuPont doesn't have a match.
It is a quality product suitable for
a finish resistant to oil and gas,
and has the factory look.
Dave \X/

